WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:05.801
Dear young people, dear believers, a
person can spend their whole life present

00:00:05.801 --> 00:00:08.795
in church and yet still be blocked.

00:00:08.795 --> 00:00:10.506
Blocked from experiencing God.

00:00:10.506 --> 00:00:12.217
Blocked from feeling God.

00:00:12.217 --> 00:00:19.917
And at the same time they can be driven
to look for answers as to why something in

00:00:19.917 --> 00:00:22.484
their spiritual life just isn’t working.

00:00:22.484 --> 00:00:29.328
I very often see people who are in church,
who practise their faith, and yet on

00:00:29.328 --> 00:00:35.317
the other hand they’re unhappy; on the
other hand they have no experience of

00:00:35.317 --> 00:00:38.740
God, and they have so, so many questions.

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:47.319
There are two things that block
us, and because of them we can’t

00:00:47.319 --> 00:00:50.401
heal our soul and our heart.

00:00:50.401 --> 00:00:55.539
One of them is that we’re
not honest with ourselves.

00:00:55.539 --> 00:00:58.622
We’re not truly honest before God.

00:00:58.622 --> 00:01:02.732
We can pretend, we can lie to others.

00:01:02.732 --> 00:01:09.411
We can even lie to ourselves, but
we can’t hide anything from God.

00:01:09.411 --> 00:01:15.063
God cannot heal and restore what
we haven’t even recognised, or

00:01:15.063 --> 00:01:18.660
what we don’t want to ask for.

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:26.525
How is it that, if we are in God’s
grace, in communion with Jesus, if

00:01:26.525 --> 00:01:32.110
we acknowledge Jesus as our Saviour,
Lord and Redeemer, how is it that

00:01:32.110 --> 00:01:37.696
we practise the faith so much and
yet we are still spiritually unwell?

00:01:37.696 --> 00:01:41.993
So spiritually unwell that, in our
weekly or fortnightly confessions,

00:01:41.993 --> 00:01:46.720
we keep going round in circles,
repeating the very same things.

00:01:47.490 --> 00:01:54.356
On the other hand, we’re capable of
putting on a false front, of lying, and we

00:01:54.356 --> 00:02:02.510
don’t want to speak and admit to God the
essence of it all – and that is who I am.

00:02:02.510 --> 00:02:07.231
Not who I present myself
as, but who I really am.

00:02:07.231 --> 00:02:11.951
If a person truly wants to grow
spiritually, then they must

00:02:11.951 --> 00:02:14.097
stop pretending and stop lying.

00:02:14.097 --> 00:02:20.535
Some figures in psychology say that
ten to fifteen per cent of us all lie.

00:02:21.234 --> 00:02:27.504
And it’s easier for people to lie
than to explain and tell the truth.

00:02:27.504 --> 00:02:30.191
And why am I saying this?

00:02:30.191 --> 00:02:36.461
Because Jesus is the one who says
that if we want to be spiritually

00:02:36.461 --> 00:02:42.283
healed, made whole, he says that
only the truth can set us free.

00:02:42.283 --> 00:02:47.657
So, dear young people, we
mustn’t put on an act before God.

00:02:47.657 --> 00:02:49.896
We mustn’t lie before God.

00:02:49.896 --> 00:02:54.375
Because, as I say, we’re committing
yet another additional sin.

00:02:55.215 --> 00:03:02.075
We keep circling around God, but
we don’t allow Him to heal us.

00:03:04.975 --> 00:03:09.928
That’s why, above all, we
need to be honest before God.

00:03:09.928 --> 00:03:17.584
If we want that real, deep healing of our
soul and heart, we have to be truthful.

00:03:17.584 --> 00:03:19.836
Let’s go step by step.

00:03:19.836 --> 00:03:24.790
How many times do we catch ourselves
saying—lying, really—“This job is

00:03:24.790 --> 00:03:30.644
great,” while on the other hand that
same job is draining us completely.

00:03:31.375 --> 00:03:34.991
On the other hand, we present
ourselves as believers.

00:03:34.991 --> 00:03:40.214
Yet our faith is so lukewarm, or
full of question marks and doubts.

00:03:40.214 --> 00:03:44.232
And so it goes round and
round, round and round.

00:03:44.232 --> 00:03:49.054
But the Lord wants to teach
us to be honest before him.

00:03:49.054 --> 00:03:53.875
And in the Letter to the Ephesians,
chapter four, it says: therefore

00:03:53.875 --> 00:03:58.697
let us put away lies and speak
the truth to one another.

00:03:58.697 --> 00:04:04.724
I don’t even need to go into how falsely
we present ourselves to each other.

00:04:04.724 --> 00:04:06.733
That’s not really the point.

00:04:06.733 --> 00:04:11.957
The point is how, before God who
searches the human heart, who sees

00:04:11.957 --> 00:04:17.582
right through every one of us, we hold
something back, we hide something, we

00:04:17.582 --> 00:04:20.395
try to explain something away to God.

00:04:20.395 --> 00:04:27.223
And in the First Letter of John it says:
if we confess our sins, he is faithful

00:04:27.223 --> 00:04:32.846
and just and will forgive us our sins
and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

00:04:32.846 --> 00:04:38.469
The only condition for true healing,
for the recovery of our soul, is to

00:04:38.469 --> 00:04:41.682
be honest before God about who I am.

00:04:41.682 --> 00:04:47.305
Yet pride slaps us in the face
so often; pride gets in the way,

00:04:47.305 --> 00:04:52.125
because those patterns of lying
teach us so much that sometimes we

00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:54.535
even come to confession and lie.

00:04:55.095 --> 00:04:58.699
And even in confession we
try to justify ourselves.

00:04:58.699 --> 00:05:00.702
Where does this come from?

00:05:00.702 --> 00:05:03.906
Think of the first people, Adam and Eve.

00:05:03.906 --> 00:05:07.110
They lived in communion,
in harmony with God.

00:05:07.110 --> 00:05:11.916
And when they sinned, each of
them felt it in their heart.

00:05:11.916 --> 00:05:17.122
The very first thing each of
them felt in their heart was that

00:05:17.122 --> 00:05:19.926
they had begun to hide from God.

00:05:19.926 --> 00:05:22.729
So they covered themselves
with fig leaves.

00:05:23.469 --> 00:05:26.297
The fig leaves represent the heart.

00:05:26.297 --> 00:05:28.653
They wrapped up their heart.

00:05:28.653 --> 00:05:35.251
Our heart is the centre of spirituality,
the centre of our relationship with God.

00:05:35.251 --> 00:05:40.435
And you see, the first consequence
of their sin was precisely

00:05:40.435 --> 00:05:42.791
that they covered their heart.

00:05:42.791 --> 00:05:43.262
Why?

00:05:43.262 --> 00:05:47.032
How did they know that
something had changed?

00:05:47.032 --> 00:05:52.687
Because each of them suddenly
felt in their heart what they were

00:05:52.687 --> 00:05:55.515
capable of doing to the other.

00:05:56.240 --> 00:06:00.553
And then each of them said,
“I’m going to protect myself.

00:06:00.553 --> 00:06:06.044
If I’m capable of hurting you, if
I’m capable of being jealous of you,

00:06:06.044 --> 00:06:11.927
if I’m capable of envying you, then
what are you capable of doing to me?”

00:06:11.927 --> 00:06:14.280
And that’s when mistrust was born.

00:06:14.280 --> 00:06:19.378
They covered their hearts with fig
leaves; they began to hide from God.

00:06:19.378 --> 00:06:24.476
That’s what it means when you
sometimes hear in a sermon: you need

00:06:24.476 --> 00:06:26.830
to strip everything off the heart.

00:06:28.370 --> 00:06:33.892
So, those fig leaves in the
Book of Genesis are, in our

00:06:33.892 --> 00:06:38.034
spirituality today, the various
defence mechanisms in our hearts.

00:06:38.034 --> 00:06:44.937
We’re so wounded and traumatised, yet we
suppress it so much that we don’t even

00:06:44.937 --> 00:06:49.539
want to show it to the Lord or admit it.

00:06:49.539 --> 00:06:53.681
And how, then, can the
Lord heal us spiritually?

00:06:53.681 --> 00:07:01.045
And as long as we keep all that buried
inside us like that, we remain weak.

00:07:01.345 --> 00:07:05.772
And then we keep repeating
the same patterns – of sin, of

00:07:05.772 --> 00:07:10.200
habits, of everything – and we
just can’t seem to be healed.

00:07:10.200 --> 00:07:12.212
We just can’t become happy.

00:07:12.212 --> 00:07:13.420
Full of fear.

00:07:13.420 --> 00:07:18.652
How is that possible, if spiritually
we’re so much in God’s grace – where

00:07:18.652 --> 00:07:21.872
does such a level of fear come from?

00:07:21.872 --> 00:07:27.105
It means that we too have covered our
hearts with something, we’re protecting

00:07:27.105 --> 00:07:29.520
ourselves, and we’re hiding from God.

00:07:29.520 --> 00:07:35.155
So how can God heal that something
if we keep hiding it, if we

00:07:35.155 --> 00:07:40.790
haven’t truly come before God and
cried out for Him to set us free?

00:07:42.250 --> 00:07:49.564
When Jesus was in the boat, when he was
out on the sea with the disciples and the

00:07:49.564 --> 00:07:55.660
storm broke, they all woke up in fear;
the apostles were afraid for their lives.

00:07:55.660 --> 00:08:01.349
How often do we today get caught
up in fear for our own lives?

00:08:01.349 --> 00:08:06.632
How often do we panic too, at
certain moments in life, when we

00:08:06.632 --> 00:08:11.915
lose our job or some other sense
of security, or someone we love?

00:08:13.270 --> 00:08:16.512
Why are we people today so full of fear?

00:08:16.512 --> 00:08:20.836
Why is it that you who are in
relationships or marriages—if you

00:08:20.836 --> 00:08:23.358
married for love—why are you so afraid?

00:08:23.358 --> 00:08:28.042
If you started a relationship with
someone out of love, why are you

00:08:28.042 --> 00:08:29.844
scared you’ll lose that person?

00:08:29.844 --> 00:08:31.645
Do you know the answer?

00:08:31.645 --> 00:08:36.690
Do you know how sensible, normal people
in the business world invest their money?

00:08:38.050 --> 00:08:44.127
They invest in a way that they’re not
fools who put everything into one person.

00:08:44.127 --> 00:08:48.179
They’re not fools who’d stake
their one shot – everything they’ve

00:08:48.179 --> 00:08:52.636
got, their capital – on a single
share that could collapse, and

00:08:52.636 --> 00:08:54.662
overnight you’re left with nothing.

00:08:54.662 --> 00:09:00.335
Why is it that some of you in
relationships and marriages are so tense

00:09:00.335 --> 00:09:03.576
with fear: what if you lose that person?

00:09:03.576 --> 00:09:08.438
Because you’ve placed all your love,
all your support, on that person.

00:09:08.438 --> 00:09:13.301
You haven’t spread your capital of
love – giving love to your husband,

00:09:13.301 --> 00:09:18.163
your wife, your fiancé or fiancée, to
friends, to other interests – instead

00:09:18.163 --> 00:09:21.810
you’ve made a god out of that one person.

00:09:21.810 --> 00:09:25.694
And of course you panic: if you
lose that person, you’ve lost

00:09:25.694 --> 00:09:27.312
the ground beneath your feet.

00:09:27.312 --> 00:09:31.520
So how is it that, even if we’ve
been healed by God’s grace,

00:09:31.520 --> 00:09:35.080
spiritually restored, we’re still
living in such fear — what if God

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:37.346
takes that person from me as well?

00:09:37.346 --> 00:09:39.288
Life is meant to have meaning.

00:09:39.288 --> 00:09:43.495
Many people can’t see any point in
carrying on when they lose someone.

00:09:43.495 --> 00:09:47.380
They can’t find their way, because
they invested everything in one person.

00:09:47.380 --> 00:09:49.944
And where is God in all that?

00:09:49.944 --> 00:09:53.975
How much do we factor God
into our sense of security?

00:09:53.975 --> 00:09:59.104
And you see it there: when the
storm broke out, in that very same

00:09:59.104 --> 00:10:01.302
boat Jesus was with the disciples.

00:10:01.302 --> 00:10:06.798
Jesus was asleep while they were waking
him up, thinking they were going to die.

00:10:06.798 --> 00:10:07.165
In…

00:10:10.715 --> 00:10:13.545
in panic and fear for their lives.

00:10:13.545 --> 00:10:15.162
And Jesus is asleep.

00:10:15.162 --> 00:10:18.801
How often do we find
ourselves in that situation?

00:10:18.801 --> 00:10:22.845
We claim we’re God’s people,
that we’re believers, and yet

00:10:22.845 --> 00:10:28.910
we panic, we make a drama of it
all, while God beside us is calm.

00:10:28.910 --> 00:10:30.931
That was their greatest weakness.

00:10:30.931 --> 00:10:35.379
That same God, Jesus, was
in that very boat with them.

00:10:35.379 --> 00:10:36.592
He sleeps peacefully.

00:10:36.592 --> 00:10:41.040
They didn’t even stop to
think that God was with them.

00:10:41.950 --> 00:10:46.040
They’re thinking about their
own lives, and yet God is in

00:10:46.040 --> 00:10:48.270
the very same boat with them.

00:10:48.270 --> 00:10:54.220
And it’s the same with you: when a
storm hits, how is it that, in every

00:10:54.220 --> 00:10:56.822
storm, we suddenly forget where God is?

00:10:56.822 --> 00:11:01.656
Do you really think God is like
that – just waiting to shove us

00:11:01.656 --> 00:11:05.746
into some fire, into some storm,
into some uncertain situation, only

00:11:05.746 --> 00:11:08.349
to leave us there and that’s it?

00:11:08.349 --> 00:11:12.439
You don’t go through happy moments,
or stormy moments, or challenges,

00:11:12.439 --> 00:11:14.670
or crises – you are never alone.

00:11:15.630 --> 00:11:21.781
There you can see how much we go round
and round in church, and yet we don’t

00:11:21.781 --> 00:11:24.313
have its basic, simple foundation in God.

00:11:24.313 --> 00:11:27.570
God is holding all of this in His hands.

00:11:27.570 --> 00:11:31.912
You can just see how wrongly we’ve
leaned on one another—making idols

00:11:31.912 --> 00:11:35.892
out of people, making gods out
of material things as well—and

00:11:35.892 --> 00:11:38.063
that’s why we’re tense and afraid.

00:11:38.063 --> 00:11:41.319
Because, in essence, our
heart doesn’t belong to God.

00:11:41.340 --> 00:11:46.283
Because if it’s that kind
of fear that paralyses you.

00:11:46.283 --> 00:11:51.227
Secondly, it strikes me how
pronounced that fear is today.

00:11:51.227 --> 00:11:57.655
And when something difficult happens
to you, what do you measure it by?

00:11:57.655 --> 00:12:03.093
I mean, the challenge, the
storm, or whatever has hit you—if

00:12:03.093 --> 00:12:08.531
you’re afraid, it’s simply a sign
you’re measuring it by yourself.

00:12:08.531 --> 00:12:15.947
Because, of course, if there’s a really
big challenge in front of you, where God’s

00:12:15.947 --> 00:12:22.375
intervention is needed, where a miracle
is needed, where God’s action is needed.

00:12:22.860 --> 00:12:25.479
Of course I can’t do that.

00:12:25.479 --> 00:12:28.099
But where’s my trust in that?

00:12:28.099 --> 00:12:31.592
That’s where fear starts—when
I measure solving problems

00:12:31.592 --> 00:12:34.211
and life by my own abilities.

00:12:34.211 --> 00:12:39.451
And then I’m aware there are
things I simply can’t sort out.

00:12:39.451 --> 00:12:42.070
That I can’t perform certain miracles.

00:12:42.070 --> 00:12:45.127
But where is God in all this?

00:12:45.127 --> 00:12:46.437
Where is God?

00:12:46.437 --> 00:12:49.930
Because fear is faith the wrong way round.

00:12:50.430 --> 00:12:55.517
Because in those moments you
start believing in failure

00:12:55.517 --> 00:12:57.778
rather than in success.

00:12:57.778 --> 00:13:06.822
And that’s why it’s so important to be
honest before God: do I really trust Him?

00:13:06.822 --> 00:13:11.343
What did Jesus hate most
about the Pharisees?

00:13:11.343 --> 00:13:13.039
He hated hypocrisy.

00:13:13.039 --> 00:13:18.126
Because they said one thing,
but felt something else.

00:13:18.126 --> 00:13:22.083
How many of us are hypocritical today?

00:13:22.083 --> 00:13:25.475
This world is full of hypocrisy.

00:13:26.295 --> 00:13:29.422
And even if we’re hypocritical
towards one another, we mustn’t

00:13:29.422 --> 00:13:30.986
be like that before God.

00:13:30.986 --> 00:13:35.052
Because the Pharisees and the others
were putting on an act before God

00:13:35.052 --> 00:13:38.492
too — pretending they were spiritual,
that they knew all the Scriptures

00:13:38.492 --> 00:13:41.619
— but that’s what irritated Jesus
most about them: their hypocrisy.

00:13:41.619 --> 00:13:45.372
They said one thing, but they
didn’t surrender the other to God.

00:13:45.372 --> 00:13:47.875
How many of us are like that today?

00:13:47.875 --> 00:13:49.333
Let’s start with ourselves.

00:13:49.333 --> 00:13:53.707
I say one thing, but in
practice is it really like that?

00:13:53.707 --> 00:13:59.174
Each of us tonight needs to look at
ourselves and ask: am I a hypocrite?

00:13:59.174 --> 00:14:01.726
Do I even want to grow spiritually?

00:14:01.726 --> 00:14:04.642
Have I got used to behaving like that?

00:14:04.642 --> 00:14:09.380
To be hypocritical, to be seen in
church, to be seen on pilgrimages,

00:14:09.380 --> 00:14:13.755
and yet I’m still a hypocrite
because I’m not sincere before God.

00:14:13.755 --> 00:14:15.715
Because I haven’t admitted it to Him.

00:14:15.715 --> 00:14:17.955
Because I haven’t cried
out to Him sincerely.

00:14:20.530 --> 00:14:24.643
So many people go to those sorts
of religious gatherings out of

00:14:24.643 --> 00:14:28.071
curiosity, out of nosiness, out
of interest in other people.

00:14:28.071 --> 00:14:31.156
And of course God can’t
do anything with that.

00:14:31.156 --> 00:14:36.983
And for the Lord to heal us, the first
thing we need to do is admit everything.

00:14:36.983 --> 00:14:41.439
When we stop lying to ourselves,
when we stop lying to God, only

00:14:41.439 --> 00:14:45.209
then do we give ourselves a
chance for real spiritual growth.

00:14:45.650 --> 00:14:49.205
It’s not a problem at
all what you’re like.

00:14:49.205 --> 00:14:53.551
It’s not a problem what you’re
carrying inside; what matters is

00:14:53.551 --> 00:14:58.686
whether you say it to God honestly,
whether you sincerely want to come

00:14:58.686 --> 00:15:01.847
out of it, whether you want to grow.

00:15:01.847 --> 00:15:06.587
That’s why it’s important that
we’re ready to walk in the truth.

00:15:06.587 --> 00:15:12.118
It says in John’s Gospel: “You will
know the truth, and the truth will

00:15:12.118 --> 00:15:18.044
set you free.” It isn’t always easy to
face yourself, to look in the mirror

00:15:18.044 --> 00:15:25.155
and see what I’m really like, but the
worst thing is if I never do it at all.

00:15:25.795 --> 00:15:29.518
And then there’s no real
spirituality in that.

00:15:29.518 --> 00:15:35.570
With some people you can see it in
their spiritual life, in confession,

00:15:35.570 --> 00:15:41.156
in everything: it’s just a kind of
folklore, not genuine spiritual growth.

00:15:41.156 --> 00:15:46.742
As long as a believer keeps on…
putting their fears first, highlighting

00:15:46.742 --> 00:15:51.397
their worries about themselves,
bringing up more and more doubts.

00:15:51.397 --> 00:15:56.517
Each of us should ask ourselves
tonight: we don’t all need

00:15:56.517 --> 00:15:58.845
healing at the same level.

00:15:59.545 --> 00:16:04.816
You know, you could interpret and
talk about three levels of healing

00:16:04.816 --> 00:16:09.208
in our spirituality, our soul,
and our relationship with God.

00:16:09.208 --> 00:16:12.283
Some people don’t move forward at all.

00:16:12.283 --> 00:16:17.993
Some are healed in two, and the
best is in all three dimensions.

00:16:17.993 --> 00:16:25.900
We carry a lot within us, and of course
a lot of it isn’t even our own fault.

00:16:25.900 --> 00:16:28.535
But God needs to heal it.

00:16:28.535 --> 00:16:32.488
How many people are suffocated
by intrusive thoughts, doubts,

00:16:32.488 --> 00:16:37.760
certain kinds of trauma — that
too needs the Lord to heal it.

00:16:37.780 --> 00:16:41.307
And that needs to be
named before the Lord.

00:16:41.307 --> 00:16:44.442
Or do you need to seek psychological help?

00:16:44.442 --> 00:16:49.536
If you can see that your mind
is blocking you, that you can’t

00:16:49.536 --> 00:16:53.847
move forward spiritually and
grow, then why not ask for help?

00:16:53.847 --> 00:16:59.334
If you can see that the area of
your traumas and your past is

00:16:59.334 --> 00:17:03.253
haunting you—false images of God, or
sinful habits and attachments—then

00:17:03.253 --> 00:17:08.740
why not come before God in truth
and say, “Heal this in me, Lord”?

00:17:10.560 --> 00:17:14.321
Why is it that you don’t even
see you’ve got certain wounds?

00:17:14.321 --> 00:17:18.082
How strange is it when someone
comes to confession and says, “I

00:17:18.082 --> 00:17:21.529
can’t forgive,” and yet they’ve
come to confession? I honestly don’t

00:17:21.529 --> 00:17:23.723
know what more to say about that.

00:17:23.723 --> 00:17:28.425
I mean, have you even thought about
it at all before you go to confession?

00:17:28.425 --> 00:17:31.245
Because that refusal to
forgive is wounding you first.

00:17:31.245 --> 00:17:34.380
OK, maybe no one ever
taught you how to forgive.

00:17:34.380 --> 00:17:38.452
Come on, before you go to
confession, have a think.

00:17:38.452 --> 00:17:41.302
How do you get rid of that?

00:17:41.302 --> 00:17:42.931
How do you forgive?

00:17:42.931 --> 00:17:44.560
Is there a way?

00:17:44.560 --> 00:17:45.374
There is.

00:17:45.374 --> 00:17:45.782
Truly.

00:17:45.782 --> 00:17:51.483
Stand in the truth before God and say,
“Lord, I’m grieving, I’m wounded; maybe

00:17:51.483 --> 00:17:57.998
I am to blame, maybe I’m not,” but all
of that is the area—like I said—where

00:17:57.998 --> 00:18:04.513
we tend to sweep it under the carpet
or just move on, and in fact never

00:18:04.513 --> 00:18:06.550
really work seriously on ourselves.

00:18:07.380 --> 00:18:11.592
You young people can still be
taught; you’re like clay that

00:18:11.592 --> 00:18:13.507
the potter can still shape.

00:18:13.507 --> 00:18:18.103
But I’ve seen so many defiant people,
so many conceited, fake “spiritual”

00:18:18.103 --> 00:18:23.464
types, the ones who won’t let anyone
tell them anything, who you’re not even

00:18:23.464 --> 00:18:26.145
allowed to point out a weakness to.

00:18:26.145 --> 00:18:30.741
That’s also a sign of spirituality:
whether, when you want to point

00:18:30.741 --> 00:18:35.720
something out to someone in love,
you can say, “Listen, you need help.”

00:18:36.485 --> 00:18:41.507
Come on, hand your life over to
the Lord a bit—tell him the truth,

00:18:41.507 --> 00:18:43.300
the real truth about yourself.

00:18:43.300 --> 00:18:48.323
What’s the point of putting on a false
front when you’re falling apart inside?

00:18:48.323 --> 00:18:51.910
I know hundreds who are in churches,
presenting themselves falsely,

00:18:51.910 --> 00:18:55.856
acting like spiritual gurus, making
themselves out to be examples of

00:18:55.856 --> 00:18:59.802
holiness, and yet inside they’re like
whitewashed tombs, full of wounds.

00:18:59.802 --> 00:19:04.466
They’re not doing it out of malice—no
one does that out of malice.

00:19:04.466 --> 00:19:06.260
Who are the strong people?

00:19:06.700 --> 00:19:08.873
Which women and men are strong?

00:19:08.873 --> 00:19:09.597
Which ones?

00:19:09.597 --> 00:19:14.305
The ones who can consciously say,
“Look, that was my weakness; I worked

00:19:14.305 --> 00:19:20.100
on it; Lord, heal it.” I’m not afraid
to say I was weak in that area.

00:19:20.100 --> 00:19:23.360
It’s not the ones who put on an act.

00:19:23.360 --> 00:19:26.982
And you who are getting into
relationships, dear young people,

00:19:26.982 --> 00:19:28.793
you can genuinely be surprised.

00:19:28.793 --> 00:19:33.501
You know, you can be in a
relationship for a year, two, three,

00:19:33.501 --> 00:19:35.675
and discover all sorts of things.

00:19:36.655 --> 00:19:39.347
And at first it all seems
idyllic, doesn’t it?

00:19:39.347 --> 00:19:43.236
You know that thing where lots of
young men have problems when they’re

00:19:43.236 --> 00:19:46.826
getting married – and girls too, I
suppose – and then, right before the

00:19:46.826 --> 00:19:51.313
wedding, that crisis hits: is this person
really for me, do I actually love her?

00:19:51.313 --> 00:19:53.407
Especially if you’ve
been together for years.

00:19:53.407 --> 00:19:57.895
You get used to the person, and then
you don’t even know any more whether

00:19:57.895 --> 00:20:01.485
you feel anything for them – love,
or whatever it is you’ve got.

00:20:03.435 --> 00:20:06.522
But it’s interesting,
that word “bride” – bride.

00:20:06.522 --> 00:20:10.932
Someone explained it really nicely:
“news” is something you know

00:20:10.932 --> 00:20:16.224
what it is – news, you know what
you’re getting from that news.

00:20:16.224 --> 00:20:21.075
But a bride is “not-news”: you
don’t know what you’re getting.

00:20:21.075 --> 00:20:25.045
You take it on and you take the risk.

00:20:25.045 --> 00:20:26.368
Do you understand?

00:20:26.368 --> 00:20:29.455
But you do it all with trust.

00:20:29.455 --> 00:20:35.188
That’s why the Lord encourages us:
how merciful it is, this adoration of

00:20:35.188 --> 00:20:41.362
ours – or any person can come, sincerely
open their soul before God, and there’s

00:20:41.362 --> 00:20:44.450
no need to be afraid of weakness.

00:20:44.450 --> 00:20:50.241
That’s why I say how wonderful it
is – those people, for me they’re

00:20:50.241 --> 00:20:54.251
strong people, who’ve been through
something weak, something hard.

00:20:54.251 --> 00:21:00.043
And psychologically that’s true: that
you can look back at your own past.

00:21:00.043 --> 00:21:05.834
Saint Francis of Assisi, in his writings,
says this – he quotes a sentence.

00:21:05.834 --> 00:21:11.626
“When I…” the document begins,
“when I was in sins…” So he starts

00:21:11.626 --> 00:21:14.745
first by looking back at his past.

00:21:15.705 --> 00:21:18.557
He has no problem
looking back at his past.

00:21:18.557 --> 00:21:23.627
How many people are there who, at some
stage in their life, come back to the

00:21:23.627 --> 00:21:27.430
Church, back to faith, and then they
start with those spiritual clichés:

00:21:27.430 --> 00:21:32.184
“I’ve been living since 2006,” “I’ve
been a new man since 2015,” and then they

00:21:32.184 --> 00:21:36.303
start counting from the date of their
conversion, their encounter with God — as

00:21:36.303 --> 00:21:38.205
if everything before that doesn’t exist.

00:21:38.205 --> 00:21:42.325
You know what I mean: they’ve
got a new birthday, you get it.

00:21:42.565 --> 00:21:45.094
He’s a new creation, he’s a miracle.

00:21:45.094 --> 00:21:48.708
And then they start counting
their life, their birthdays and

00:21:48.708 --> 00:21:50.153
celebrations from that moment.

00:21:50.153 --> 00:21:53.044
Of course, symbolically,
I know what they mean.

00:21:53.044 --> 00:21:56.657
But hang on — the Lord
has delivered me from sin.

00:21:56.657 --> 00:22:01.355
I’ve been Stjepan from conception
right up to now, to this very moment.

00:22:01.355 --> 00:22:05.691
Because anyone who wipes out their
past, who can’t look at their

00:22:05.691 --> 00:22:07.860
sinful past, hasn’t been healed yet.

00:22:07.860 --> 00:22:08.572
Believe me.

00:22:08.572 --> 00:22:12.491
Those who come out with those
spiritual clichés and “erase” the

00:22:12.491 --> 00:22:17.122
past, who only emphasise the present
as if they’re up in seventh heaven

00:22:17.122 --> 00:22:19.259
— great — you’ll crash sooner or later.

00:22:19.259 --> 00:22:23.178
You can’t erase the past, because
that’s where the testimony is.

00:22:23.178 --> 00:22:26.384
That was me, Lord — that
sinner, in that situation.

00:22:26.384 --> 00:22:29.590
I admit it; heal me, and we move on.

00:22:29.590 --> 00:22:35.290
And for your sake I will bear witness
to what you have done in my life.

00:22:35.290 --> 00:22:36.715
That’s the right way.

00:22:36.715 --> 00:22:40.079
And don’t erase the past, don’t
deny the wounds, don’t suppress

00:22:40.079 --> 00:22:41.608
your feelings — none of that.

00:22:41.608 --> 00:22:43.443
Pour it all out before Jesus.

00:22:43.443 --> 00:22:47.725
I don’t know, when someone says, “Oh,
adoration is boring,” what do you mean?

00:22:47.725 --> 00:22:51.700
I can’t even get through listing all
the problems and wounds and everything

00:22:51.700 --> 00:22:55.676
I’ve piled up in a week before
I’ve finished pouring my heart out.

00:22:55.676 --> 00:22:58.735
That only means you come
before Jesus like a mummy.

00:23:00.959 --> 00:23:05.842
However perfect you are, my sunshine,
if you’ve come today, if you’ll be

00:23:05.842 --> 00:23:09.597
at adoration later, however perfect
you are and psychologically stable,

00:23:09.597 --> 00:23:14.855
and you come from a wonderful family
and go to Mass every day, you’re

00:23:14.855 --> 00:23:18.235
spiritually strong—still, somehow
there’s always something to hand over

00:23:18.235 --> 00:23:21.240
to Jesus, some truth that sets me free.

00:23:24.310 --> 00:23:28.740
I really like those people who go to
prayer groups or to adoration and all

00:23:28.740 --> 00:23:33.170
that, and they only ever pray for others
— like they’ve got no problems at all.

00:23:33.170 --> 00:23:34.351
Well done, my dear.

00:23:34.351 --> 00:23:38.190
Me, the moment I start praying for
others as well, I’ve got problems

00:23:38.190 --> 00:23:42.030
— I’ve got problems even when I’m
praying for myself, and then when I’m

00:23:42.030 --> 00:23:44.097
praying for others on top of that.

00:23:44.097 --> 00:23:48.527
So it’s strange to me when some people
have nothing to pray for themselves about.

00:23:48.527 --> 00:23:51.185
Mate, I’ve got plenty — and
I think everyone does.

00:23:51.185 --> 00:23:55.024
Because if we take the whole day,
from morning onwards… and the only

00:23:55.024 --> 00:23:59.750
thing I want to say at the end is:
learn to always tell God the truth.

00:24:00.469 --> 00:24:04.970
Who you are, what you are, just as
you are – God loves you like that.

00:24:04.970 --> 00:24:05.270
Amen.

